State-owned mining companies in the
Democratic Republic of Congo are in talks with unidentified
private groups about funding mineral exploration projects in the
country, Mines Minister  Martin Kabwelulu  said in a speech at the
Mining Indaba conference in  Cape Town  today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
